cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the role of creativity in the mobile service domain and focuses on evaluating mobile service ideas from young children. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper involves analyzing and evaluating a large set of mobile service ideas.
